In a call between President Obama and King Salman bin Abdulaziz al-Saud of Saudi Arabia, they discussed recent developments in Yemen. The President reaffirmed the strong friendship between the two countries and emphasized the US commitment to Saudi Arabia's security. They also talked about the recent adoption of a resolution on Yemen in the UN Security Council and the next steps in resuming the political transition in Yemen through talks facilitated by the United Nations. Both leaders agreed on the importance of achieving lasting stability in Yemen through a negotiated political solution involving all parties as outlined in the GCC Initiative. They also discussed the need to address the humanitarian needs of the Yemeni people.